## 2. P0: WeightEntry Full Persistence

### Before
```
pipe_{ns}_hebbian_weight: weight_id, from, to, weight_value
```
5 critical fields lost when harness terminates.

### After
```
pipe_{ns}_hebbian_weight: weight_id, from, to, weight_value,
    inertia_mass, cumulative_potential, external_hits,
    internal_hits, stability_ticks, is_dead_node
```

#### [NEW] `pipe_{ns}_dead_node_trace` table

```sql
CREATE TABLE pipe_{ns}_dead_node_trace (
    trace_id, run_id, from_entity_id, to_entity_id,
    inertia_mass, cumulative_potential,
    external_hits, internal_hits, weight_value,
    tick_suspected, tick_recovered, recovery_cause
);
```

**Every dead node (M_eff > 0.9 × M_max) now has a complete forensic record** including:
- Which edge died (from_entity_id → to_entity_id)
- Why it died (cumulative_potential, external_hits)
- When it died (tick_suspected)
- Whether it recovered (tick_recovered, recovery_cause)

